## Summary: Reading Time Calculation and Display in iskrib_v3

### 1. **`.reading-time-text` CSS Class**

The `.reading-time-text` class is used in multiple components to style the reading time display. Here are the relevant CSS definitions:

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\postcards.css` (lines 652-660)
```css
.reading-time-text{
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    color: var(--accent-sage);
    letter-spacing: 0.01rem;
}
```

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Bookmarks\bookmarks.css` (lines 257-265)
```css
.bookmark-card-footer .reading-time-text{
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-ui, sans-serif);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    color: var(--accent-sage, #6b8f71);
    letter-spacing: 0.01rem;
}
```

### 2. **Components Using `.reading-time-text`**

The reading time display appears in these components:

1. **PostCards** (`C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\PostCards.jsx` - lines 866-868)
   - Uses within `.reading-time-container` div
   - Displays on feed post cards

2. **Bookmarks** (`C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Bookmarks\Bookmarks.jsx` - lines 231-233)
   - Shows reading time for bookmarked posts
   - Located in bookmark card footer

3. **ExplorePage** (`C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\explore\ExplorePage.jsx` - lines 112-114, 173-175, 593-595)
   - Displays reading time on explore feed results
   - Multiple instances for different view layouts

4. **ContentView** (`C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\ContentViewer\ContentView.jsx` - line 520)
   - Uses `cv-read-time` class (different styling)
   - Displays reading time in post metadata alongside publish date

### 3. **Reading Time Calculation Logic**

**Location:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\calculateReadingTime.js`

**Function:** `CalculateText(text)`

**Algorithm:**
```javascript
const CalculateText = (text) => {
    const wordPerMin = 150;  // Average reading speed: 150 words per minute
    const words = text.trim().split(/\s+/).length;  // Count whitespace-separated tokens
    const minutes = words / wordPerMin;
    const readingTime = Math.ceil(minutes);  // Round up to nearest minute

    if(readingTime > 1){
        return `${readingTime} mins read`;
    }
    return `${readingTime} min read`;
}
```

**Key Details:**
- **Fixed reading speed:** 150 words per minute (industry standard)
- **Calculation:** Word count divided by 150, rounded up
- **Minimum:** Always shows "1 min read" (even for very short content)
- **Format:** Singular "min" for 1 minute, plural "mins" for 2+ minutes

### 4. **Input Data Sources**

The `CalculateText` function receives different text inputs depending on context:

- **PostCards & Bookmarks:** `previewText` - the preview text stored in database
- **ContentView (detail page):** `postData?.wholeText` - full text content extracted from Lexical JSON via `ParseContent()`
- **ExplorePage:** `previewText` - from API response

**Note:** `preview_text` is persisted at write time during upload (stored in database for cards/feeds), while `wholeText` is computed on-demand from `content` for full post views.

### 5. **CSS Styling - Reading Time Container**

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\postcards.css` (lines 642-660)
```css
.reading-time-container{
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.7rem;
    background-color: var(--bg-pill);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-left: auto;  /* Positioned on right side of card footer */
}
```

**File:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\ContentViewer\contentviewer.css` (lines 179-191)
```css
.cv-read-time {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}
```

### 6. **Calculation Type: Dynamic (Not Static)**

The reading time **is calculated dynamically** from content length/word count:
- It's **not** a static value stored in the database
- Calculated on the client-side every time the component renders
- Uses the actual text content (preview or full) as input
- Changes if content length changes

### 7. **Mobile Responsiveness**

Mobile adjustments in `postcards.css` (lines 1101-1114):
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .reading-time-container{
        position: absolute;
        top: 0.55rem;
        right: 0.55rem;
        /* ... absolute positioning for top-right corner */
    }
    .reading-time-text{
        font-size: 0.58rem;  /* Slightly smaller on mobile */
        white-space: nowrap;
    }
}
```

---

**In summary:** The reading time feature is entirely client-side, using a simple 150 WPM formula applied to the text content available to each component, displayed in pill-shaped containers with a sage green accent color.
